    "rtw_universe_collapsing": "4 RTW products killed in last 18 months (ANA Jun 2025, SQ Star May 2024, SkyTeam Go Round 2024-25, SQ Pacific Circle likely 2024-25). Star Alliance + oneworld + Lufthansa M&M + Qantas are the safe bets.",
    "for_pure_around_the_world": "Star Alliance RTW (most flexible, online-bookable) or oneworld Explorer (continent-based, online via rtw.oneworld.com).",
    "for_premium_cabin_optimization": "Lufthansa M&M (fixed 400k J / 540k F) or Qantas (35k mi cap, 318k for J). M&M is better for transferable-currency holders. Qantas is cheaper for short-band trips.",
    "cheap_business_class_rtw": "Star Alliance RTW Special Business at the 26,000 mi distance band is widely considered the cheapest J-class RTW. Quote varies significantly by routing and origin country; check staralliance.com/en/book-fly for the actual price for the specific itinerary before recommending.",
    "for_asia_pacific_multi_stop": "Star Alliance Circle Pacific OR oneworld Circle Pacific (travel agent only) OR JAL Mileage Bank multi-carrier (cheapest at 25k Y / 48k J for under 4000mi distance).",
    "for_regional_north_america": "Aeroplan distance-based (6k Y starting under 500mi) or Iberia partner chart for AA short hops (12k Y for under 650mi RT).",
    "for_intra_europe": "Iberia Plus on Iberia metal off-peak: 3,500 Avios for under 650mi single-direction. Cheapest intra-EU option after BA Avios.",
    "avoid_aeromexico": "Phone-only booking, kilometers (not miles), reportedly difficult agents. Only consider if SkyTeam alignment is mandatory.",
    "avoid_iberia_partner_awards": "Non-refundable. Iberia metal awards have a EUR 25 change fee but ARE refundable. Plan accordingly.",
    "tpm_vs_great_circle": "JAL/Star Alliance/oneworld use IATA TPM (Ticketed Point Mileage). Aeroplan uses actual flown distance. TPM can differ from gcmap.com great-circle by a few percent and affects which distance band you fall into. Use scripts/calc_distance.py for great-circle estimates; verify with airline before booking.",
    "stopover_definition": "Most programs define a stopover as a layover of 24+ hours.",
    "circle_vs_rtw": "'Circle' products require all 3 areas of the Pacific Rim, smaller distance caps, but typically cheaper than full RTW. Geographically constrained to one hemisphere.",
    "purchase_deadline": "Star Alliance RTW: at least 72 hours before first departure. oneworld Explorer: similar. Plan ahead.",
    "child_pricing": "Star Alliance RTW: 75% for ages 2-11, 10% for infants without seat. Other programs vary."
